# Dar-Ul-Quran — Cursor AI Rules

## Project

Islamic educational organization website. Next.js 15 App Router + React 19 + Sanity v6 CMS + Tailwind CSS v4. Fully RTL (Urdu/Arabic). TypeScript strict mode.

---

## Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 15 App Router (no Pages Router)
- **UI:** React 19 — default to Server Components; `"use client"` only for interactivity
- **CMS:** Sanity v6 with next-sanity v13 — all queries in `sanity/lib/queries.ts`
- **Styles:** Tailwind CSS v4 via PostCSS plugin — brand colors `dq-*` (gold palette)
- **Language:** TypeScript v6, strict, no `any`
- **Rich Text:** @portabletext/react
- **Images:** next/image + @sanity/image-url (`urlFor`)
- **Icons:** lucide-react only
- **Font:** Noto Nastaliq Urdu (Google Fonts) — `font-urdu` Tailwind class

---

## File Structure (critical paths)

```
app/(site)/layout.tsx         → site shell (Header + Footer)
app/(site)/page.tsx           → homepage
sanity/lib/queries.ts         → ALL GROQ queries (never inline)
sanity/lib/client.ts          → safeFetch wrapper (returns null on missing config)
sanity/lib/image.ts           → urlFor() image builder
components/ui/Reveal.tsx      → scroll-triggered animations
components/ui/ContentCard.tsx → reusable card
tailwind.config.ts            → custom tokens (dq-* colors, animations)
app/globals.css               → keyframe definitions
```

---

## Rules

### Always
- Server Components by default — add `"use client"` only when needed
- All GROQ in `sanity/lib/queries.ts` — no inline queries in pages
- Use `safeFetch` from `sanity/lib/client.ts` — handles null gracefully
- Use `<Link>` not `<a>`, `<Image>` not `<img>`
- Use `ms-*`/`me-*` (margin-inline-start/end) for RTL-safe spacing
- Add `alt` text to every Sanity image field
- Use `dq-*` color tokens — never raw hex for brand colors
- TypeScript `type` keyword for props, not `interface`
- `leading-[1.8]` or higher for Urdu/Arabic body text

### Never
- No `any` or `@ts-ignore` without explanation
- No `getServerSideProps`/`getStaticProps` — App Router only
- No `useEffect` for data fetching — use async Server Components
- No hardcoded phone/email/social links — everything from Sanity siteSettings
- No `console.log` in committed code
- No `styled-components` or `emotion` — Tailwind only
- No `@tailwindcss/typography` — prose styles live in globals.css
- No `"use client"` on layout.tsx or page.tsx files without interactivity
- No direct `import` of server modules (sanity client, nodemailer) in client components

---

## RTL Rules

- HTML root: `lang="ur" dir="rtl"` — never override with `dir="ltr"` without reason
- Use `rtl:` Tailwind prefix for RTL-specific overrides
- `flex-row` reverses visually in RTL — use `flex-row-reverse` for LTR visual order
- `rotate-180` on chevrons/arrows in RTL navigation contexts

---

## Sanity Schema Rules

- Every public content type needs `slug` with `isUnique`
- Parent references (`course.parent`, `service.parent`) use `weak: false`
- `order` number field on all list types for manual sort
- `seo: { title, description }` inline on every content type
- `body` is always Portable Text array

---

## Environment Variables (required)

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_SANITY_PROJECT_ID
NEXT_PUBLIC_SANITY_DATASET
SANITY_API_TOKEN
EMAIL_USER / EMAIL_PASS / EMAIL_TO
```

---

## Common Gotchas

1. Tailwind v4 uses new syntax: `bg-black/50` not `bg-opacity-50`
2. `cdn.sanity.io` must be in `next.config.ts` remotePatterns for images
3. Catch-all `[...slug]` params are `string[]` — join with `/` for paths
4. Layout ISR is 300s — nav changes take up to 5 min to reflect
5. Noto Nastaliq Urdu has large vertical metrics — always test with real Urdu text
